        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 7:06PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 705 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Woodbury, or over Huntington Station, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brentwood, Commack, Huntington Station, Plainview, Hauppauge,
Ronkonkoma, Syosset, Huntington, Westbury, Stony Brook, Northport,
Oyster Bay, Hicksville, Dix Hills, and Smithtown.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for
southeastern New York.</instruction>
